---
description: Ensure test coverage when adding or changing API endpoints
globs: 
  - client/src/db/api.ts
  - client/src/db/hooks/*.ts
alwaysApply: true
---

# Test Coverage

When adding a new API endpoint or modifying an existing one in `client/src/db/api.ts`:

1. Check if a test file exists for the module (e.g. `api.test.ts`)
2. If tests exist, add or update test cases covering the new/changed function
3. If no test file exists yet, create one alongside the source file

When adding or modifying a custom hook in `client/src/hooks/`:

1. Check for a corresponding test file (e.g. `useRounds.test.ts`)
2. Add or update tests for new behavior, especially CRUD operations and error handling

Test files live next to the source file they cover. Use the project's configured test runner.
